In this article, President Barack Obama discusses the measures his government has taken to protect the American people. He mentions the investigation into the failed terrorist attack in Detroit and the reorientation of efforts in the fight against Al Qaeda in Afghanistan and Pakistan. Obama emphasizes the importance of international alliances in pressuring extremists worldwide. He also discusses the ongoing investigation into the Christmas Day incident and the suspect's affiliation with Al Qaeda in the Arabian Peninsula. Obama highlights the need to strengthen the alliance with Yemen and work together to combat terrorism. He mentions the progress made in disrupting terrorist networks and saving American lives. Obama acknowledges that the task of protecting the nation is ongoing and encourages necessary questions, changes, and debates to ensure the best way to protect the country. He urges unity and determination in the face of adversity and emphasizes the importance of the American spirit. The article concludes with Obama expressing his hope for a united and safe country in the new year.